      "writtenOn": "2021-01-14T20:58:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we need an option here to enable compression and keep it off by default, or at least keep it off for JSON responses by default: on GAE gzip compression is done by Appengine itself. It will be unwise to do it on our side (will be paying for CPU $$$): https://cloud.google.com/appengine/docs/standard/go111/how-requests-are-handled#response_compression\n\nI verified it by looking at cr-buildbucket response headers for SearchBuild RPC, they have \"content-encoding: gzip\".\n\nluci/server.Server can set it to true when it detects it is not on GAE.",
